  "text": "We characterized the nucleic acid composition of three sets of wild type (wt) and mutant PFV particles harboring individual GR box deletions (ΔGRI, ΔGRII, ΔGRIII) ( Figure 1A ), generated by transfecting cells with different amounts of transfer vector, ranging over three orders of magnitude ( Figure 2 ). The amount of Gag, Pol and Env packaging constructs was kept constant in all samples, which resulted in a similar virus production and particle release in all samples ( [CITATION_1] , data not shown).",
